SYSTEM OVERVIEW
1. Business Context
In dynamic business environments, maintaining accurate records of employee presence is crucial for operational efficiency and payroll accuracy. This system modernizes traditional attendance tracking by providing:
Key Functional Components:
1.1 Employee Information Management 
o	Detailed profiles and employment data for all staff members
o	Integration with department and role assignments
1.2.	Real-Time Attendance Tracking 
o	Digital time clock for check-in/check-out timestamps
o	Automatic work hour calculations
o	Overtime and late arrival detection
1.3.	Shift Scheduling 
o	Tools to assign and manage work shifts
o	Ensure adequate coverage across departments
o	Support for multiple shift types (Morning, Day, Evening, Night)
1.4.	Leave Approval Workflow 
o	Structured process for leave requests
o	Manager review and approval system
o	Leave balance tracking
1.5.	Compliance & Security 
o	Role-based access control (Admin, Manager, Employee)
o	Data integrity and security measures
o	Audit trail for all transactions
1.7. System Benefits
By integrating these elements, the system provides:
â€¢	Critical information for attendance pattern recognition
â€¢	Enhanced employee accountability
â€¢	Informed decision-making for workforce scheduling
â€¢	Improved productivity tracking and analysis
2. TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE
Technology Stack
Backend Technologies
â€¢	Programming Language: Java 17+
â€¢	Framework: Spring Boot 3.x
â€¢	Database: MySQL 8.0+ / Microsoft SQL Server
â€¢	Authentication: JWT (JSON Web Tokens)
â€¢	Security: Spring Security with BCrypt password encoding
â€¢	API Architecture: RESTful services
â€¢	Database Connectivity: JDBC (Java Database Connectivity)
Frontend Technologies
â€¢	Core: Vanilla JavaScript (ES Modules)
â€¢	Markup: HTML5
â€¢	Styling: CSS3
â€¢	Architecture: Single Page Application (SPA)
â€¢	HTTP Client: Fetch API
Desktop Interface (Optional)
â€¢	Framework: JavaFX (for administrative desktop interface)
â€¢	Purpose: Complex management tasks and advanced reporting
Development Tools
â€¢	IDEs: IntelliJ IDEA, Eclipse, Visual Studio Code
â€¢	Build Tool: Maven 3.6+
â€¢	Version Control: Git & GitHub
â€¢	Database Tools: MySQL Workbench, SQL Server Management Studio
â€¢	API Testing: Postman, curl, built-in API Test Helper
*System Architecture
