3.STRUCTURE
Complete Project Structure
Employee_Attendance/
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ README.md                          This documentation file
â”œâ”€â”€ pom.xml                            Maven project configuration
â”œâ”€â”€ server.js                          Frontend static file server 
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ src/main/                          Backend source code
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ java/
â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ employeeAttendanceSystem/
â”‚   â”‚       â””â”€â”€ com/employeeSystem/
â”‚   â”‚           â”œâ”€â”€ Application.java            Spring Boot main class
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚
â”‚   â”‚           â”œâ”€â”€ Config/                     Configuration classes
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â””â”€â”€ SecurityConfig.java     Spring Security config
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚
â”‚   â”‚           â”œâ”€â”€ controller/                 REST API Controllers
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ AuthController.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ AttendanceController.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ DepartmentController.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ EmployeeController.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ HolidayController.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ LeaveRecordController.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ ShiftController.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â””â”€â”€ UserLoginController.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚
â”‚   â”‚           â”œâ”€â”€ model/                      DTOs (Data Transfer Objects)
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ AttendanceRequestDTO.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ AttendanceResponseDTO.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ DepartmentRequestDTO.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ DepartmentResponseDTO.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ EmployeeRequestDTO.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ EmployeeResponseDTO.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â””â”€â”€ ... (other DTOs)
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚
â”‚   â”‚           â”œâ”€â”€ repository/                 Data Access Layer
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ entity/                 Database entities
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ AttendanceEntity.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ DepartmentEntity.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ EmployeeEntity.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ HolidayEntity.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ LeaveRecordEntity.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ ShiftEntity.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ UserLoginEntity.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”‚
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ AttendanceRepository.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ DepartmentRepository.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ EmployeeRepository.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â””â”€â”€ ... (repository interfaces)
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚
â”‚   â”‚           â”œâ”€â”€ service/                    Business Logic Layer
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ impl/                   Service implementations
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ AttendanceService.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ AuthService.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ DepartmentService.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â””â”€â”€ ... (service interfaces)
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚
â”‚   â”‚           â”œâ”€â”€ Security/                   Security components
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ JwtTokenProvider.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ JwtAuthenticationFilter.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ JwtAuthenticationEntryPoint.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚   â””â”€â”€ TokenBlacklist.java
â”‚   â”‚           â”‚
â”‚   â”‚           â””â”€â”€ Request/                    Request/Response wrappers
â”‚   â”‚               â”œâ”€â”€ AuthResponse.java
â”‚   â”‚               â”œâ”€â”€ LoginRequest.java
â”‚   â”‚               â””â”€â”€ RegisterRequest.java
â”‚   â”‚
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ resources/
â”‚       â””â”€â”€ application.properties             Database & server config
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ target/                                    Maven build output (generated)
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ Frontend Files (HTML/CSS/JS)               Frontend application
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ UserLogin.html                         Login/Register page
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Dashboard.html                         Main dashboard
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Employees.html                         Employee management
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Attendance.html                        Attendance tracking
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Department.html                        Department management
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Shifts.html                            Shift management
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Holiday.html                           Holiday management
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ LeaveRecords.html                      Leave request management
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ ApiTestHelper.html                     API connectivity tester
â”‚   â”‚
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ css/
â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ styles.css                         Global stylesheet
â”‚   â”‚
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ js/
â”‚       â”œâ”€â”€ api.js                             API communication layer
â”‚       â”œâ”€â”€ App.js                             Common utilities
â”‚       â”œâ”€â”€ Charts.js                          Chart rendering (optional)
â”‚       â””â”€â”€ SideBar.js                         Sidebar component
â”‚
â””â”€â”€ .git/                                      Git version control
Key File Descriptions
Backend Files
Application.java
â€¢	Main entry point for Spring Boot application
â€¢	Configures component scanning and auto-configuration
SecurityConfig.java
â€¢	Configures Spring Security
â€¢	Defines CORS policy
â€¢	Sets up JWT authentication filter chain
â€¢	Configures password encoding (BCrypt)
Controllers
â€¢	Handle incoming HTTP requests
â€¢	Map to service layer methods
â€¢	Return appropriate HTTP responses
â€¢	Apply role-based security annotations
DTOs (Data Transfer Objects)
â€¢	Define request/response structures
â€¢	Separate database entities from API contracts
â€¢	Include validation annotations
Entities
â€¢	Map to database tables
â€¢	Define relationships between tables
â€¢	Include JPA annotations (if using JPA)
Repositories
â€¢	Interface with database
â€¢	Execute SQL queries
â€¢	Return entity objects
Services
â€¢	Implement business logic
â€¢	Validate inputs
â€¢	Coordinate between controllers and repositories
â€¢	Apply transaction management
Frontend Files
server.js
â€¢	Simple .js HTTP server
â€¢	Serves static files (HTML/CSS/JS)
â€¢	Runs on port 8081
HTML Pages
â€¢	Each page corresponds to a feature module
â€¢	Use ES Modules for JavaScript
â€¢	Link to shared CSS and JS files
js/api.js
â€¢	Wraps Fetch API
â€¢	Automatically adds JWT token to requests
â€¢	Handles common HTTP errors
â€¢	Provides typed API methods
js/App.js
â€¢	Authentication utilities (checkLogin, getUser)
â€¢	Role-based access control (checkRole)
â€¢	Redirect logic
css/styles.css
â€¢	Global styles for all pages
â€¢	Responsive design utilities
â€¢	Component-specific styles
4.INSTALLATION & SETUP
Test Backend API:Test using curl
curl http://localhost:8081/pi/auth/login
Expected: Error message (endpoint requires POST with body)
http://localhost:8081/api/auth/login
â€¢	You should see an error page (expected, as this endpoint requires POST request)
Frontend Setup & Execution
Step 3: Start Frontend Server
Frontend server running at http://localhost:8081
Open a browser and navigate to http://localhost:8081/Dashboard.html after logging in.
Step 4: Access Application in Browser
Open your web browser
Navigate to login page: http://localhost:8081/UserLogin.html
You should see:
   - Login form with UserID and Password fields
   - "Login" and "Register" tabs
   - "Remember me" checkbox
   - "Forgot password?" link
First Login
Step 1: Choose Test Account
Login as ADMIN:
UserID: 1
Password: 123456
Step 2: Click "Sign In" Button
Step 3: Verify Successful Login
Expected behavior:
- Redirect to Dashboard.html
- See statistics cards (Total Employees, Attendance, etc.)
- Sidebar navigation visible
- User avatar and role displayed in top-right corner
Step 4: Test Navigation
Click through sidebar menu:
- âœ… Dashboard
- âœ… Employees
- âœ… Attendance
- âœ… Department
- âœ… Shifts
- âœ… Holiday
- âœ… Leave Records
5. TEST CREDENTIALS & ROLE PERMISSIONS
5.1 ADMIN Role
Login Credentials:
UserID: 1
Username: nnahuy
Password: 123456
Role: ADMIN
Full System Access:
| Feature | Create | Read | Update | Delete |
|---------|--------|------|--------|--------|
| Employees | âœ… | âœ… | âœ… | âœ… |
| Departments | âœ… | âœ… | âœ… | âœ… |
| Shifts | âœ… | âœ… | âœ… | âœ… |
| Holidays | âœ… | âœ… | âœ… | âœ… |
| Attendance (All) | âœ… | âœ… | âœ… | âœ… |
| Leave Requests (All) | âœ… | âœ… | âœ… | âœ… |
Specific Permissions:
- âœ… View all dashboard statistics
- âœ… Access all pages without restriction
- âœ… Manage employee profiles (add/edit/delete)
- âœ… Assign employees to departments
- âœ… Create and modify shifts
- âœ… Mark attendance for ANY employee
- âœ… Approve/Deny ALL leave requests (all departments)
- âœ… Manage company-wide holidays
- âœ… Generate all types of reports
- âœ… Modify system settings
Restrictions:
- âŒ None - Full administrative access
Use Cases:
- HR Director managing entire organization
- System Administrator configuring system
- Executive viewing company-wide reports
