5.2 UserLogin.html - Authentication Page
Purpose: Entry point for user authentication and registration
Features:
* Login Tab 
o	UserID input field (numeric)
o	Password input field (masked)
o	"Remember me" checkbox
o	"Forgot password?" link
o	"Sign In" button
*	Register Tab 
o	Username input
o	Password input
o	Role selection dropdown (Employee/Manager)
o	Terms agreement checkbox
o	"Create Account" button
Technical Details:
â€¢	Submits POST request to /api/auth/login
â€¢	Stores JWT token in localStorage
â€¢	Stores user object (userId, username, role) in localStorage
â€¢	Redirects based on role: 
o	ADMIN/MANAGER â†’ Dashboard.html
o	EMPLOYEE â†’ Employees.html (own profile)
Security:
NN
Continue
â€¢	Passwords transmitted over HTTPS (in production)
â€¢	JWT token with expiration
â€¢	Role-based redirect prevents unauthorized access
User Flow:
1. User enters credentials
2. Click "Sign In"
3. Frontend sends POST /api/auth/login
4. Backend validates credentials
5. Backend returns JWT token + user info
6. Frontend stores token & user in localStorage
7. Frontend redirects to appropriate page
5.3 Dashboard.html - Overview & Statistics
Purpose: Central hub showing system-wide or department-specific metrics
Role-Based Display:
ADMIN View:
â€¢	âœ… Total Employees (company-wide)
â€¢	âœ… Today's Attendance count
â€¢	âœ… Pending Leave Requests
â€¢	âœ… Upcoming Holidays
â€¢	âœ… Department-wise employee distribution chart
â€¢	âœ… Quick action buttons for all features
MANAGER View:
â€¢	âœ… Total Employees (department only)
â€¢	âœ… Today's Attendance (department only)
â€¢	âœ… Pending Leave Requests (department only)
â€¢	âœ… Upcoming Holidays (company-wide)
â€¢	âœ… Quick actions for department tasks
EMPLOYEE View:
â€¢	âŒ Redirected to Employees.html (own profile)
Statistics Cards:
1.	Total Employees 
o	Count of active employees
o	Blue color scheme
o	Icon: ðŸ‘¥
2.	Today's Attendance 
o	Number of check-ins for current date
o	Green color scheme
o	Icon: âœ“
3.	Pending Leave Requests 
o	Count of requests awaiting approval
o	Orange color scheme
o	Icon: ðŸ“‹
4.	Holidays 
o	Total company holidays
o	Red color scheme
o	Icon: ðŸŽ‰
Upcoming Holidays Section:
â€¢	Lists next 5 holidays
â€¢	Shows holiday name and date
â€¢	Scrollable if more than 5
Department Chart:
â€¢	Bar chart showing employees per department
â€¢	Uses Chart.js or canvas rendering
â€¢	Color-coded bars
Quick Actions Panel:
â€¢	"Add New Employee" button â†’ Employees.html
â€¢	"Mark Attendance" button â†’ Attendance.html
â€¢	"Manage Leaves" button â†’ LeaveRecords.html
â€¢	"Add Holiday" button â†’ Holiday.html
System Info Panel:
â€¢	Last updated timestamp
â€¢	System status indicator
â€¢	Version information
Auto-refresh:
â€¢	Dashboard data refreshes every 30 seconds
â€¢	Visual indicator during refresh
* Employees.html - Employee Management
Purpose: Manage employee records and profiles
Role-Based Features:
ADMIN Access:
â€¢	âœ… View all employees in table
â€¢	âœ… Add new employee (modal form)
â€¢	âœ… Edit employee details
â€¢	âœ… Delete employee
â€¢	âœ… Search/filter employees
â€¢	âœ… Assign employees to departments
MANAGER Access:
â€¢	âœ… View employees in managed department
â€¢	âŒ Add/Edit/Delete disabled
EMPLOYEE Access:
â€¢	âœ… View own profile only
â€¢	âŒ All management features hidden
â€¢	Page title changes to "My Profile"
Employee Table Columns:
Column	Description
ID	Employee ID (auto-generated)
Name	First Name + Last Name
Email	Contact email
Department	Department name
Joining Date	Date hired
Status	Active/Inactive badge
Actions	Edit/Delete buttons
